Date:  22/1/2006
Source:  Sunday Star Times
Author:
Vol / Page:  A11
Edition:
Quote:  Before Winston said he "would not accept the baubles of office", the word referred to showy trinkets or trifles. Now it has been redefined to mean large powerful positions much greater than either warranted or deserved and the trinkets now refers to junkets of the first class travelling variety.
